.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-JOBS" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.34" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-jobs \- List tracked jobs under the current repo tree
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose jobs [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Scan the current repository tree for tracked hpc\-compose submissions and list the recorded jobs without querying the scheduler.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
\fBlist\fR
List tracked jobs discovered under the repo tree. See hpc\-compose\-jobs\-list(1).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose jobs list
hpc\-compose jobs list \-\-disk\-usage
hpc\-compose jobs list \-\-format json
.fi
